---
const pageTitle = "Selenium Automation Assessment | QA ALIGN";
const pageDescription =
  "Get a Selenium automation assessment with trust level, issue breakdown, flaky test risk, CI diagnosability review, and estimated cost to fix.";

const assessmentHref = "/thank-you";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

    <meta property="og:title" content={pageTitle} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={pageDescription} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />

    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #0b0e14;
        --panel: #111827;
        --panel-2: #151d2b;
        --panel-3: #0f1724;
        --text: #f8fafc;
        --muted: #a7b0c0;
        --soft: #cbd5e1;
        --border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        --border-strong: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18);
        --accent: #38bdf8;
        --accent-2: #22c55e;
        --warning: #f59e0b;
        --danger: #ef4444;
        --shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
        --radius: 20px;
        --max: 1120px;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12), transparent 34rem),
          radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1), transparent 30rem),
          var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        font-family:
          Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
          "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .site-shell {
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      .topbar {
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: rgba(11, 14, 20, 0.86);
        backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 20;
      }

      .topbar-inner {
        max-width: var(--max);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 16px 22px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 18px;
      }

      .brand {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        min-width: 0;
      }

      .brand-mark {
        width: 34px;
        height: 34px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.28), rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2));
        border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      .brand-text {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .brand-name {
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        line-height: 1;
      }

      .brand-tagline {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 12px;
        margin-top: 3px;
      }

      .topnav {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 14px;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .topnav a:hover {
        color: var(--text);
      }

      .topnav .nav-cta {
        color: #061018;
        background: var(--accent);
        padding: 9px 14px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-weight: 800;
      }

      .section {
        max-width: var(--max);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 72px 22px;
      }

      .hero {
        padding-top: 84px;
        padding-bottom: 54px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.08fr) minmax(320px, 0.92fr);
        gap: 34px;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        color: var(--accent);
        border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.24);
        background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.08);
        border-radius: 999px;
        padding: 7px 11px;
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 800;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
      }

      .eyebrow-dot {
        width: 8px;
        height: 8px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: var(--accent-2);
        box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.65);
      }

      h1,
      h2,
      h3,
      p {
        margin-top: 0;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px);
        line-height: 0.96;
        letter-spacing: -0.065em;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }


      .hero-subheadline {
        margin: -8px 0 22px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 38px);
        line-height: 1.1;
        font-weight: 900;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      .hero-lede {
        color: var(--soft);
        font-size: clamp(18px, 2vw, 21px);
        max-width: 690px;
        margin-bottom: 26px;
      }

      .hero-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 12px;
        margin: 30px 0 22px;
      }

      .button {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        min-height: 46px;
        padding: 12px 18px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
        color: var(--text);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
        font-weight: 800;
        transition:
          transform 0.16s ease,
          background 0.16s ease,
          border-color 0.16s ease;
      }

      .button:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
        border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.26);
      }

      .button.primary {
        color: #041018;
        background: var(--accent);
        border-color: transparent;
        box-shadow: 0 14px 40px rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.24);
      }

      .button.primary:hover {
        background: #67d8ff;
      }

      .hero-note {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 14px;
        margin: 0;
      }

      .hero-note strong {
        color: var(--text);
      }


      .hero-video-card {
        width: 100%;
        transform: translate(34px, -42px);
      }

      .hero-video-frame {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
        border-radius: 22px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: #000;
        border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.22);
        box-shadow:
          0 28px 90px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55),
          0 0 70px rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12);
      }

      .hero-video-frame iframe {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        border: 0;
        display: block;
      }

      .hero-video-caption {
        margin: 14px 0 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      .decision-card {
        background:
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025)),
          var(--panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .decision-card-header {
        padding: 18px 18px 14px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .decision-card-title {
        font-weight: 900;
      }

      .badge {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        border-radius: 999px;
        padding: 6px 10px;
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 900;
        letter-spacing: 0.03em;
        border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
      }

      .badge.medium {
        color: #fbbf24;
        background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1);
        border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.28);
      }

      .decision-card-body {
        padding: 18px;
      }

      .metric-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
      }

      .metric {
        background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 14px;
        padding: 13px;
      }

      .metric-value {
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 900;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      .metric-label {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 12px;
        margin-top: 2px;
      }

      .issue-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 10px;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        list-style: none;
      }

      .issue {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
        gap: 10px;
        align-items: center;
        padding: 12px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 14px;
      }

      .issue-rank {
        width: 26px;
        height: 26px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
        background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 900;
      }

      .issue-title {
        font-weight: 800;
      }

      .issue-meta {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 12px;
      }

      .issue-count {
        font-weight: 900;
        color: var(--soft);
        font-size: 13px;
      }

      .trust-line {
        margin-top: 18px;
        padding: 14px;
        border-radius: 14px;
        background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.08);
        border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.18);
        color: var(--soft);
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .trust-line strong {
        color: var(--accent-2);
      }

      .strip {
        padding-top: 0;
        padding-bottom: 36px;
      }

      .proof-strip {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 14px;
      }

      .proof-item {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 18px;
      }

      .proof-kicker {
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 900;
        font-size: 13px;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .proof-item p {
        color: var(--soft);
        margin: 0;
      }

      .section-head {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
      }

      .section-kicker {
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 900;
        font-size: 13px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 48px);
        line-height: 1.02;
        letter-spacing: -0.05em;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
      }

      .section-head p {
        color: var(--soft);
        font-size: 18px;
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .problem-panel {
        background: var(--panel-3);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        padding: 28px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.95fr 1.05fr;
        gap: 24px;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      }

      .problem-copy p {
        color: var(--soft);
        font-size: 18px;
      }

      .signal-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 10px;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        list-style: none;
      }

      .signal-list li {
        padding: 14px 14px 14px 42px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 14px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
        color: var(--soft);
        position: relative;
      }

      .signal-list li::before {
        content: "!";
        position: absolute;
        left: 14px;
        top: 14px;
        width: 19px;
        height: 19px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
        background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.13);
        color: var(--warning);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 900;
      }

      .review-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 14px;
      }

      .review-card {
        min-height: 210px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .review-number {
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 900;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }

      .review-card h3 {
        font-size: 20px;
        line-height: 1.15;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .review-card p {
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .output {
        background:
          linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.08), transparent 36%),
          linear-gradient(315deg, rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.08), transparent 38%),
          var(--panel);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }

      .output .section {
        padding-top: 78px;
        padding-bottom: 78px;
      }

      .output-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.86fr 1.14fr;
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .output-card {
        background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        padding: 24px;
      }

      .output-list {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        list-style: none;
        display: grid;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .output-list li {
        display: flex;
        gap: 10px;
        color: var(--soft);
      }

      .check {
        color: var(--accent-2);
        font-weight: 900;
      }

      .report-preview {
        background: #071018;
        border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.18);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .report-preview-top {
        padding: 16px 18px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 14px;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .report-preview-top strong {
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }

      .report-preview-body {
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .report-block {
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
      }

      .report-block:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .report-label {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 900;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .report-block p {
        color: var(--soft);
        margin: 0;
      }

      .cost-grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: 8px;
      }

      .cost-row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
        gap: 10px;
        color: var(--soft);
      }

      .cost-row strong {
        color: var(--text);
      }

      .path-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 14px;
      }

      .path-card {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 22px;
      }

      .path-card h3 {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .path-card p {
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .cta-band {
        max-width: var(--max);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 24px 22px 82px;
      }

      .cta-card {
        background:
          linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.16), rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1)),
          var(--panel-2);
        border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
        border-radius: 26px;
        padding: clamp(28px, 5vw, 46px);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .cta-card h2 {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .cta-card p {
        color: var(--soft);
        font-size: 18px;
        margin-bottom: 0;
        max-width: 760px;
      }

      .footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .footer-inner {
        max-width: var(--max);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 22px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 16px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 920px) {
        .topnav {
          display: none;
        }

        .hero,
        .problem-panel,
        .output-grid,
        .cta-card {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .hero {
          padding-top: 56px;
        }

        .proof-strip,
        .review-grid,
        .path-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .metric-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .cta-card .button {
          width: 100%;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 560px) {
        .section {
          padding: 52px 18px;
        }

        .topbar-inner,
        .cta-band,
        .footer-inner {
          padding-left: 18px;
          padding-right: 18px;
        }

        .hero-actions .button {
          width: 100%;
        }

        .problem-panel,
        .output-card,
        .report-preview-body {
          padding: 18px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="site-shell">
      <header class="topbar">
        <div class="topbar-inner">
          <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="QA ALIGN home">
            <span class="brand-mark">QA</span>
            <span class="brand-text">
              <span class="brand-name">QA ALIGN™</span>
              <span class="brand-tagline">Trust Through Evidence</span>
            </span>
          </a>

          <nav class="topnav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
            <a href="/offerings/">Offerings</a>
            <a href="#review">What gets reviewed</a>
            <a href="#report-output">Report output</a>
            <a class="nav-cta" href={assessmentHref}>Free Assessment</a>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main>
        <section class="section hero">
          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">
              <span class="eyebrow-dot"></span>
              Selenium Automation Assessment
            </div>

            <h1>Automation Trust Issues?</h1>
            <p class="hero-subheadline">Get a Selenium Automation Assessment</p>

            <p class="hero-lede">
              QA ALIGN reviews your Selenium framework, CI failures, flaky tests,
              locator strategy, and release signal quality — then gives you a clear
              trust level, issue breakdown, and estimated cost to fix.
            </p>

            <div class="hero-actions">
              <a class="button primary" href={assessmentHref}>Get the Free Selenium Assessment</a>
              <a class="button" href="#report-output">See What the Report Includes</a>
            </div>

            <p class="hero-note">
              <strong>Output:</strong> TRUST LEVEL → ISSUE BREAKDOWN → ESTIMATED COST TO FIX
            </p>
          </div>

          <aside class="hero-video-card" aria-label="QA ALIGN report video">
            <div class="hero-video-frame">
              <iframe
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2TQUZDrKTaw?rel=0&modestbranding=1"
                title="QA ALIGN Report Demo"
                loading="lazy"
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                allowfullscreen
              ></iframe>
            </div>

            <p class="hero-video-caption">
              Watch QA ALIGN turn automation evidence into a trust level, issue breakdown,
              and estimated cost-to-fix report.
            </p>
          </aside>
        </section>

        <section class="section strip" aria-label="Assessment proof points">
          <div class="proof-strip">
            <div class="proof-item">
              <div class="proof-kicker">Not generic QA advice</div>
              <p>Every assessment is framed around release trust, failure evidence, and cost to fix.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="proof-item">
              <div class="proof-kicker">Built for Selenium reality</div>
              <p>Legacy suites, brittle locators, slow CI, reruns, and mixed framework ownership.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="proof-item">
              <div class="proof-kicker">Decision-ready output</div>
              <p>Designed to help technical leaders choose stabilize, modernize, or rebuild.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="problem">
          <div class="section-head">
            <div class="section-kicker">The real problem</div>
            <h2>Selenium still works. Your release signal may not.</h2>
            <p>
              Most Selenium suites do not fail because Selenium is “bad.”
              They fail because the automation system lost its contracts.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="problem-panel">
            <div class="problem-copy">
              <h3>When Selenium becomes a release risk</h3>
              <p>
                A Selenium suite can have hundreds or thousands of tests and still fail
                to answer the only question leadership cares about:
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Can we release?</strong>
              </p>
              <p>
                When every failed run requires reruns, Slack threads, tribal knowledge,
                or manual interpretation, the problem is no longer test coverage.
                The problem is trust.
              </p>
            </div>

            <ul class="signal-list">
              <li>CI failures that require reruns before anyone believes them</li>
              <li>Flaky UI tests blocking releases or creating false alarms</li>
              <li>Selectors breaking after minor UI changes</li>
              <li>Slow suites that discourage frequent execution</li>
              <li>Poor screenshots, traces, logs, or failure artifacts</li>
              <li>Results that do not separate product bugs from framework problems</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="review">
          <div class="section-head">
            <div class="section-kicker">Assessment scope</div>
            <h2>What the Selenium Assessment Reviews</h2>
            <p>
              QA ALIGN looks at the system around Selenium — not just the test code.
              The goal is to determine whether the suite can produce trusted evidence.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="review-grid">
            <article class="review-card">
              <div class="review-number">01</div>
              <h3>Locator Strategy</h3>
              <p>
                CSS/XPath fragility, accessibility locator usage, selector consistency,
                naming patterns, and long-term maintainability risk.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="review-card">
              <div class="review-number">02</div>
              <h3>Failure Diagnosability</h3>
              <p>
                Screenshots, videos, traces, logs, error messages, rerun dependency,
                and whether failures can be debugged without another execution.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="review-card">
              <div class="review-number">03</div>
              <h3>CI Reliability</h3>
              <p>
                Pipeline behavior, artifact retention, retry patterns, environment
                assumptions, timeout behavior, and inconsistent execution signals.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="review-card">
              <div class="review-number">04</div>
              <h3>Framework Structure</h3>
              <p>
                Page objects, fixtures, helpers, config, test data setup, shared
                utilities, and the amount of hidden behavior in the framework.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="review-card">
              <div class="review-number">05</div>
              <h3>Release Signal Quality</h3>
              <p>
                Whether test results can support GO / WARN / BLOCK decisions or
                still require manual interpretation before release.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="review-card">
              <div class="review-number">06</div>
              <h3>Modernization Path</h3>
              <p>
                Whether to stabilize Selenium, selectively migrate high-value flows,
                or rebuild around a more deterministic automation architecture.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="output" id="report-output">
          <div class="section">
            <div class="section-head">
              <div class="section-kicker">Report output</div>
              <h2>You do not get generic QA advice. You get a release decision view.</h2>
              <p>
                The assessment output is designed for technical leaders who need to
                decide whether to repair, modernize, or replace a Selenium automation system.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="output-grid">
              <div class="output-card">
                <h3>What you receive</h3>
                <ul class="output-list">
                  <li><span class="check">✓</span><span>Trust level: LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH</span></li>
                  <li><span class="check">✓</span><span>Top automation risks by category</span></li>
                  <li><span class="check">✓</span><span>Issue breakdown with occurrence counts</span></li>
                  <li><span class="check">✓</span><span>Estimated cost to fix</span></li>
                  <li><span class="check">✓</span><span>Recommended stabilization path</span></li>
                  <li><span class="check">✓</span><span>Modernization recommendation if Selenium is no longer the right center of gravity</span></li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="report-preview">
                <div class="report-preview-top">
                  <strong>Example Assessment Output</strong>
                  <span class="badge medium">MEDIUM</span>
                </div>

                <div class="report-preview-body">
                  <div class="report-block">
                    <div class="report-label">Primary Risk</div>
                    <p>
                      The Selenium suite can detect failures, but the failure artifacts
                      are not strong enough to support release decisions without reruns
                      or manual interpretation.
                    </p>
                  </div>

                  <div class="report-block">
                    <div class="report-label">Top Issues</div>
                    <ul class="issue-list">
                      <li class="issue">
                        <span class="issue-rank">1</span>
                        <span>
                          <span class="issue-title">Locator fragility</span>
                          <span class="issue-meta">High maintenance risk</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="issue-count">18x</span>
                      </li>
                      <li class="issue">
                        <span class="issue-rank">2</span>
                        <span>
                          <span class="issue-title">Environment-sensitive failures</span>
                          <span class="issue-meta">CI confidence risk</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="issue-count">9x</span>
                      </li>
                      <li class="issue">
                        <span class="issue-rank">3</span>
                        <span>
                          <span class="issue-title">Missing diagnostic artifacts</span>
                          <span class="issue-meta">Debug without rerun gap</span>
                        </span>
                        <span class="issue-count">7x</span>
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>

                  <div class="report-block">
                    <div class="report-label">Estimated Fix</div>
                    <div class="cost-grid">
                      <div class="cost-row">
                        <span>Baseline stabilization</span>
                        <strong>1–2 weeks</strong>
                      </div>
                      <div class="cost-row">
                        <span>Good release signal</span>
                        <strong>3–5 weeks</strong>
                      </div>
                      <div class="cost-row">
                        <span>Modernized framework path</span>
                        <strong>6–10 weeks</strong>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
          <div class="section-head">
            <div class="section-kicker">Recommended paths</div>
            <h2>Three outcomes from the assessment</h2>
            <p>
              The page should not promise a migration before the system is reviewed.
              The assessment determines the right path.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="path-grid">
            <article class="path-card">
              <h3>Stabilize Selenium</h3>
              <p>
                Best when the framework still has usable structure but needs locator,
                data, CI, and artifact discipline restored.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="path-card">
              <h3>Modernize selectively</h3>
              <p>
                Best when high-value flows need stronger evidence while legacy Selenium
                remains in place during transition.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="path-card">
              <h3>Rebuild the release signal</h3>
              <p>
                Best when the current suite produces too much noise to support confident
                GO / WARN / BLOCK decisions.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="cta-band">
          <div class="cta-card">
            <div>
              <h2>Find out whether your Selenium suite is still worth trusting.</h2>
              <p>
                Submit your repo URL, site URL, and notes. QA ALIGN will review the
                automation system and return a structured assessment with trust level,
                issue breakdown, and estimated cost to fix.
              </p>
            </div>

            <a class="button primary" href={assessmentHref}>Get the Free Selenium Assessment</a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>

      <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-inner">
          <span>QA ALIGN™ — Trust Through Evidence</span>
          <span>Deterministic automation assessments for release confidence.</span>
